Alot of the things in FF the movie needed explaining in order for them to continue the story. Alot of things weren't even explained. Why were there only 8 spirits, if the phantoms were ghosts how come ballistic weapons and guns harmed them? Maybe the second one is not that important.<br>
And in a 40 hour square game, most of the dialogue is to do with the story. Townpeople and bosses make up a very small portion of it. In final fantasy 7 the northern crater, lifestream sequence, and soldier scenes take at least a half hour to complete EACH. that's an hour and half total and 75% of an average movie. And all those scenes are, are window after window of script. If all of that was spoken words it may even amount to more. And those are very small portions of the game. You could never fit the rest of it into another half hour.<br>
In a sci-fi or fantasy movie, the most important thing is the setting. The setting is what makes it sci-fi or fantasy. If you (the audience) can't figure out what the setting is then the story means nothing.<br>
If the characters never explained the 8 spirits, the audience would be confused as to why the heck they were looking for little plants, birds, and whatnot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/urebelliousangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rebellious Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/15/01 2:31:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://repressedinsolence.0catch.com/eye.JPG height=47 width=89></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Final Fantasy movie...</span><hr size=1> I keep telling my friends the reason FF:TSW didn't so well in the US was because &quot;most people aren't ready for it yet.&quot;  This is one of those occassions when they stare at me for a moment and then laugh uneasily.  But I still think it's true.  Granted, the storyline was slightly weak, the dialogue could've been better, and Aki's &quot;crying&quot; was comical at best...  But I liked the movie overall.  Then again, I like just about any movie where most of the characters die, especially if the significant other of the main character, or the main character him/herself dies.  (Ex: Braveheart, Armageddon)  Yeah, I know, I'm a sick child.  *shrug*  I still liked the movie.<br>
